================================================================================
Bundled RGAA dataset
================================================================================

The files src/data/rgaa.json and src/data/glossary.json are derived from the
official Référentiel Général d'Amélioration de l'Accessibilité (RGAA), version
4.1.2, published by the Direction interministérielle du numérique (DINUM /
DISIC) of the French government.

Source: https://github.com/DISIC/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr
        (RGAA/criteres.json, RGAA/glossaire.json)

The RGAA content is published under the Licence Ouverte / Open License 2.0
(Etalab): https://www.etalab.gouv.fr/licence-ouverte-open-licence/

ultra11y restructures this content (composing dotted criterion ids, deriving
plain-text titles, flattening WCAG/technique references, stripping glossary
HTML) but does not alter its meaning. Attribution: « RGAA 4.1.2 — DINUM ».

================================================================================
Inspiration
================================================================================

The audit report format is inspired by the RGAA audit conventions of DINUM and
the etalab-ia/skills RGAA skill; the native-HTML-first authoring rules are
adapted from the SocialGouv/skills rgaa-html-css skill. No source code was
copied from either project; only public conventions and rule lists were adapted.
